item.title: Ensuring the Success of Human Spaceflight with Astronaut Fred Gregory
item.description:
Ensuring the Success of Human Spaceflight with Astronaut Fred Gregory

The 2024 Astronaut Scholarship Foundation Award Presentation and Lecture

"Ensuring the Success of Human Spaceflight"
Featuring Astronaut Fred Gregory

Program includes:

-Astronaut Scholarship award presentation
-Presentation by Fred Gregory
-Q&A
-Brief reception

About the Astronaut:

Fred Gregory is a trailblazing American astronaut and retired U.S. Air Force Colonel. His storied career began with his selection as one of NASA’s first African American astronauts in 1978. Gregory first made history in 1985 as the pilot of STS-51-B aboard the Challenger, and later became the first African American to command a spaceflight during STS-33 on Discovery in 1989. His third mission, STS-44 on Atlantis, was another milestone in his illustrious career. Beyond his achievements in space, Gregory held key leadership roles at NASA, including Deputy Administrator from 2002 to 2005, during which he briefly served as Acting NASA Administra"

From Wednesday, September 25, 2024 7:00 PM to 9:00 PM EDT at Hartley Room, Denius Student Center.

Sea Turtle Preservation Society

STPS holds a monthly membership too keep the membership informed of STPS activities, STPS has a speaker each month who discusses environmental and conservation issues affecting marine life. We need volunteers to run the laptops - ensure the speaker's presentation is loaded onto the laptop, sign up for a Zoom session using the STPS account, loginto the Zoom meeting, and monitor the chat line of the Zoom session. Ensure the microphone is working and all the equipment is hooked up to the projector in the room.

Please email Louise Schuster at volunteer@seaturtlespacecoast.org about your availability. We would like to have two computer saavy volunteers are each meeting.

Louise Ann Schuster - 717-21-4769 - volunteer@seaturtlespacecoast.org

Seminole Ranch Hike

The Club will be going on an 8 Mile Day Hike, at the Seminole Ranch conservation area. This will be a moderate to easy route with well-maintained trails. Make sure to bring ample water for multiple hours in the Florida sun, and dress appropriately in active clothing and comfortable shoes. We will be meeting at 8:45 AM out front of the SUB to provide Carpool rides to this event to those that are interested. We will be departing from the school at 9 AM, and meeting anyone who can provide their own transport at the Parking lot at 10 AM. The hike will last 3-4 hours depending on the group's speed.

item.title: Sea Turtle Preservation Society Monthly Membership Meeting
item.description:
Sea Turtle Preservation Society Monthly Membership Meeting

Sea Turtle Preservation Society

STPS holds a monthly membership too keep the membership informed of STPS activities, STPS has a speaker each month who discusses environmental and conservation issues affecting marine life. We need volunteers to run the laptops - ensure the speaker's presentation is loaded onto the laptop, sign up for a Zoom session using the STPS account, loginto the Zoom meeting, and monitor the chat line of the Zoom session. Discovery Day Fall 2024

Discovery Day is Florida Tech's largest open house-style admission event, held twice annually on two Saturdays, once in the fall (November) and once in the spring (April). This structured, full-day event provides prospective students and their families the opportunity to dive in, learn about, and get a true feel for Florida Tech's vibrant campus and community. Attendees can look forward to admission and financial aid presentations, campus tours, department meetings, lunch with current students, and an academic program fair, offering a unique opportunity to gain a true sense of what Florida Tech has to offer.

 

Registration opens on September 1, 2024 and is required for attendance. Prospective attendees can register on the Admissions webpage. Additional information on Discovery Day can be found on the Discovery Day webpage. If you need assistance please contact the admission team at 321-674-8030.

item.title: Sea Turtle Preservation Society Monthly Membership Meeting
item.description:
Sea Turtle Preservation Society Monthly Membership Meeting

Sea Turtle Preservation Society

STPS holds a monthly membership too keep the membership informed of STPS activities, STPS has a speaker each month who discusses environmental and conservation issues affecting marine life. We need volunteers to run the laptops - ensure the speaker's presentation is loaded onto the laptop, sign up for a Zoom session using the STPS account, loginto the Zoom meeting, and monitor the chat line of the Zoom session. Ensure the microphone is working and all the equipment is hooked up to the projector in the room.

Please email Louise Schuster at volunteer@seaturtlespacecoast.org about your availability. We would like to have two computer saavy volunteers are each meeting.

Louise Ann Schuster - 717-21-4769 - volunteer@seaturtlespacecoast.org

From Thursday, December 5, 2024 6:00 PM to 9:00 PM EST at Satellite Beach Municipal Complex, Civic Center.
